WEBVTT

00:05.100 --> 00:05.896
Time's running out.

00:05.930 --> 00:07.397
Ray Allen for three
at the buzzer.

00:07.440 --> 00:08.566
Yes!
Oh!

00:08.600 --> 00:10.033
Heat win by two.

00:10.070 --> 00:12.129
Carmelo with a running hook!

00:20.680 --> 00:21.647
CARRIE:
You're forgetting.

00:21.680 --> 00:22.817
I hit the Red Sox

00:22.850 --> 00:24.181
on Wednesday.

00:24.220 --> 00:26.256
Plus, I nailed that
three-team parlay

00:26.290 --> 00:29.828
of the A's, Jays and
the Reds on Friday, right?

00:29.860 --> 00:32.055
Which would put
my new total at...

00:33.660 --> 00:37.266
See, that is a very
nice number, Zeke.

00:37.300 --> 00:39.632
All right, give me the Mets
tonight, two times.

00:39.670 --> 00:40.637
Okay.

00:40.670 --> 00:42.809
Bye.

00:42.840 --> 00:44.262
That was my bank.

00:44.310 --> 00:45.402
Your bank's not
like my bank.

00:45.440 --> 00:47.476
Oh, you have no idea.

00:47.510 --> 00:48.329
So what do we got?

00:48.380 --> 00:51.599
Old guy took a noser
from the 12th floor.

00:51.650 --> 00:52.742
Eliot has us out here

00:52.780 --> 00:54.247
because he's some
big-shot doctor

00:54.280 --> 00:55.440
on the faculty
at Algonquian.

00:55.480 --> 00:57.448
What's his name?

00:57.490 --> 00:58.843
Uh, hold on.

00:58.890 --> 01:01.154
Lustig.
Eugene Lustig.

01:01.190 --> 01:03.226
LUSTIG:
"So while we will always

01:03.260 --> 01:05.387
"gaze ahead with wonder

01:05.430 --> 01:08.319
"at the great uncharted
terrain of the future,

01:08.360 --> 01:10.396
"I believe it will
soon be pOSSIble,

01:10.430 --> 01:12.739
"by unlocking
the secrets of memory,

01:12.770 --> 01:15.637
"to turn our gaze behind us

01:15.670 --> 01:19.276
"and bathe in new sunlight

01:19.310 --> 01:22.108
the hidden landscapes
of our past."

01:22.150 --> 01:23.276
Thank you.

01:25.850 --> 01:27.545
MAN:
I'm so sorry, folks,

01:27.580 --> 01:29.548
Dr. Lustig has
another engagement.

01:29.590 --> 01:30.340
Thank you so much
for coming.

01:30.390 --> 01:31.687
LUSTIG: Bye-bye.
Take care. Thanks.

01:31.720 --> 01:33.153
CARRIE: _
Dr. Lustig. HI.

01:33.190 --> 01:34.555
I'm sorry, Dr. Lustig
has a plane to catch.

01:34.590 --> 01:37.150
Dr. Lustig, I just need
to talk to you for one minute.

01:37.190 --> 01:39.294
"Thank you for your
kind words, Chancellor.

01:39.330 --> 01:41.218
"It's great to be
back at my alma mater

01:41.260 --> 01:43.296
"under such
a bluebird sky.

01:43.330 --> 01:44.524
"30 years ago,

01:44.570 --> 01:46.788
"when the late Professor
Ed Hartung introduced me

01:46.840 --> 01:48.796
to the mysteries
of the human memory..."

01:48.840 --> 01:51.400
This is the speech I gave
at Cornell last week.

01:51.440 --> 01:53.305
It hasn't been
published yet.

01:53.340 --> 01:54.807
_Did someone
give you a copy?

01:54.840 --> 01:56.671
No.

01:58.550 --> 02:01.246
I think I'll, uh,
catch a later flight.

02:11.730 --> 02:13.425
Jo?

02:13.460 --> 02:14.825
Hi.

02:14.860 --> 02:16.566
I saw him speak at the Y.

02:16.600 --> 02:18.295
He was very impressive.

02:18.330 --> 02:20.469
Yes, he was.

02:21.940 --> 02:23.601
Pushed, jumped

02:23.640 --> 02:25.699
or fell-- that is the question.

02:25.740 --> 02:26.934
In my opinion,

02:26.980 --> 02:29.346
his injuries are
consistent with a high fall,

02:29.380 --> 02:30.802
but anything else,

02:30.850 --> 02:32.715
tomorrow will tell.

02:35.720 --> 02:38.518
Did they, um...
did they see anything?

02:38.550 --> 02:40.586
The landing, not the dismount.

02:41.590 --> 02:43.478
Al, I-I knew him.

02:44.530 --> 02:46.623
It was 2004.

02:46.660 --> 02:48.799
Year and a half after...

02:48.830 --> 02:51.628
I quit the force.

02:51.670 --> 02:53.297
Quit you.

02:53.340 --> 02:54.466
I was a wreck.

02:54.500 --> 02:56.331
I mean, every, uh...

02:56.370 --> 02:58.235
every bad thing
that had ever happened to me,

02:58.270 --> 02:59.874
every mistake I had ever made

02:59.910 --> 03:02.743
was running in my head
on a loop.

03:06.450 --> 03:07.678
And then I heard about

03:07.720 --> 03:10.587
this neurologist,
Eugene Lustig, and...

03:12.020 --> 03:14.659
So I tracked him down.

03:14.690 --> 03:16.658
I figured, you know,
why not...

03:16.690 --> 03:19.523
donate my body to science
before I was dead?

03:21.530 --> 03:23.669
Maybe in the process,
I wouldn't crack up.

03:23.700 --> 03:27.397
Then I-I joined
a research group,

03:27.440 --> 03:29.260
with ﬁve other people.

03:29.310 --> 03:30.561
The first of
what became known as

03:30.610 --> 03:33.704
Highly Superior
Autobiographical Memory.

03:33.740 --> 03:35.503
HSAM.

03:35.540 --> 03:37.246
Were you still
in touch with him?

03:37.280 --> 03:39.646
No, not for years.
It's...

03:42.520 --> 03:46.411
Gene Lustig is the reason
I didn't crack up.

03:51.430 --> 03:53.625
Not exactly lived-in.

03:53.660 --> 03:56.595
You'd expect
a few books at least.

03:56.630 --> 03:57.824
Know if he was married?

03:57.870 --> 03:59.599
He was.

03:59.640 --> 04:00.789
Getting divorced,
actually.

04:00.840 --> 04:02.398
I just talked to the neighbor.

04:02.440 --> 04:03.737
She said Lustig moved in
a month ago

04:03.770 --> 04:04.839
after breaking up with his wife.

04:04.870 --> 04:06.406
Neighbor know him well?

04:06.440 --> 04:08.772
It occurred to me,
but she says no.

04:08.810 --> 04:10.277
But she did say
Lustig was having

04:10.310 --> 04:11.277
a bunch of health problems,

04:11.310 --> 04:13.039
was down in
the dumps lately.

04:13.080 --> 04:14.718
And judging by
how clean this place is--

04:14.750 --> 04:16.889
no sign of struggle
or forced entry--

04:16.920 --> 04:18.012
kind of makes you wonder.

04:18.050 --> 04:19.779
What are you saying

04:22.590 --> 04:24.956
You find a suicide note?

04:24.990 --> 04:26.696
Any kind of drugs
for depression?

04:26.730 --> 04:28.994
No, but, you know,
still doesn't mean...

04:29.030 --> 04:30.520
Then I'm not buying it.

04:33.070 --> 04:35.561
AL:
Railing's too high.

04:35.600 --> 04:38.034
We can_ cross
off "accndent."

04:44.480 --> 04:45.549
WEBSTER:
...came down 12 stories.

04:45.580 --> 04:47.514
Pushed, jumped or fell...

04:47.550 --> 04:49.745
There was a geranium
right there.

04:49.790 --> 04:50.609
There was a plant.

04:50.650 --> 04:51.844
How you got geranium,
I don't know.

04:51.890 --> 04:54.051
Because I saw it down below.

04:54.090 --> 04:56.320
Bits of clay, dirt...

04:59.660 --> 05:03.619
Gene's attacker...

05:03.670 --> 05:06.537
rushes him and
throws hIm over,

05:06.570 --> 05:07.889
but Gene grabs
on to the railing.

05:07.940 --> 05:09.760
So in order
to break his grip,

05:09.810 --> 05:11.835
the attacker picks up the
first thing he can find,

05:11.870 --> 05:13.508
and... smash.

05:13.540 --> 05:15.474
The flower pot
goes over, too.

05:15.510 --> 05:17.774
We don't know the flower pot
is connected to this,

05:17.810 --> 05:19.675
we don't know how many
people were involved,

05:19.720 --> 05:21.540
we don't know for sure
he didn't jump.

05:21.580 --> 05:23.787
We'll get Webster on it,

05:23.820 --> 05:25.640
and CSU will take a look
at the clay fragments.

05:25.690 --> 05:27.487
I knew Gene Lustig.

05:27.520 --> 05:29.351
He was one of the most
pOSItlve, Vibrant people

05:29.390 --> 05:30.584
I have ever met.

05:30.630 --> 05:31.881
He gave me hope
when I had none,

05:31.930 --> 05:34.353
and that's not
easy to do.

05:34.400 --> 05:37.722
He didn't commit suicide.

05:55.680 --> 05:57.011
Three fingers are broken,

05:57.050 --> 05:58.608
each between the first
and second knuckle.

05:58.650 --> 06:01.983
Also...

06:02.020 --> 06:06.753
I found topsoil in his scalp
and under his shirt collar.

06:06.800 --> 06:10.463
Absent your flower pot theory,
I came up with nothing.

06:10.500 --> 06:12.388
His neighbor said he had
some kind of health problems.

06:12.440 --> 06:14.169
Did you find anything?
Oh.

06:14.200 --> 06:16.031
Jumped right out at me.

06:16.070 --> 06:17.537
He had cancer.

06:17.570 --> 06:18.537
Cancer?

06:18.570 --> 06:19.537
Mm-hmm.

06:19.580 --> 06:20.899
See those little white dots?

06:20.940 --> 06:22.441
Radioactive tubes.

06:22.480 --> 06:23.549
Brachytherapy.

06:23.580 --> 06:24.672
Prostate cancer.

06:24.710 --> 06:26.143
Exactly.
Treated early,

06:26.180 --> 06:28.444
the success rate is...

06:28.480 --> 06:30.846
95% after 15 years.

06:30.890 --> 06:32.915
So then that would not
be a reason

06:32.960 --> 06:34.757
for him to jump off a balcony.

06:34.790 --> 06:35.757
Right.

06:35.790 --> 06:37.849
Oh, Carrie, I'm so sorry.

06:37.890 --> 06:39.494
Al told me you knew him.

06:39.530 --> 06:42.090
Were you his student?

06:42.130 --> 06:44.064
More like his object of study.

06:44.100 --> 06:47.490
I can't imagine
you being a lab rat.

06:47.540 --> 06:48.461
I was difficult.

06:48.500 --> 06:50.730
I tried to chew through
the bars on my cage.

06:52.010 --> 06:54.205
Look, I know I'm not
the detective on this,

06:54.240 --> 06:55.172
but I'm with you.

06:55.210 --> 06:57.508
Your friend had help
going over that balcony.

06:59.620 --> 07:01.474
Carrie!
Oh.

07:01.520 --> 07:03.147
: Sorry,
I didn't mean to startle you.

07:03.190 --> 07:04.543
Hi. That's okay.

07:04.590 --> 07:05.739
May I call you Carrie?

07:05.790 --> 07:06.814
Yeah, sure, sure.

07:06.860 --> 07:07.884
Great. Come on.

07:07.920 --> 07:09.524
I want to tell you all about

07:09.560 --> 07:11.858
this little study
I've dreamed up.
Okay.

07:11.890 --> 07:14.450
No needles, no electrodes,
I assure you.

07:14.500 --> 07:15.558
Oh, well, that's...
that's a relief.

07:15.600 --> 07:19.058
Just simple questions
to gauge the capacity

07:19.100 --> 07:20.897
of your marvelous mind.

07:20.940 --> 07:23.465
I don't know
about "marvelous."

07:23.510 --> 07:25.239
Save the modesty
for Terry Gross.

07:25.270 --> 07:27.135
This is science.

07:27.180 --> 07:29.876
Next week, I want to have you
meet the others.

07:29.910 --> 07:31.047
Others?

07:31.080 --> 07:33.947
Yeah, the other study subjects.

07:33.980 --> 07:37.689
Oh, did you think
you were alone?

07:45.930 --> 07:47.522
It's okay.

07:47.560 --> 07:48.754
You can go.

07:48.800 --> 07:50.267
I'll take good care of him.

07:50.300 --> 07:51.722
Thanks, Jo.

07:56.640 --> 07:59.803
Nothing on the surveillance
video from Lustig's building.

07:59.840 --> 08:02.138
The camera in the lobby
shows him entering alone.

08:02.180 --> 08:04.068
No cameras at all in
the basement or garage.

08:04.110 --> 08:05.748
Any prints off
the flower pot?

08:05.780 --> 08:07.577
CSU has to
reassemble it first.

08:07.620 --> 08:08.848
We're talking pellets.

08:08.880 --> 08:10.711
I wouldn't
hold your breath.

08:10.750 --> 08:12.786
Well, it looks like
the ex-wife's clean.

08:12.820 --> 08:14.651
Friends say the divorce
was amicable,

08:14.690 --> 08:16.282
and she's been in Europe
for five weeks.

08:16.320 --> 08:17.218
So she's out of
the picture.

08:17.260 --> 08:19.285
But I wouldn't come to you
without something.

08:19.330 --> 08:22.527
Been digging around
at the university.

08:22.570 --> 08:25.130
Meet Alwyn Pierce.

08:25.170 --> 08:27.058
Assistant Professor of Neurology
at Algonquian.

08:27.100 --> 08:29.068
Former graduate student
of our Dr. Lustig.

08:29.100 --> 08:30.533
Something of a protg.

08:30.570 --> 08:32.299
Lustig had high hopes
for this lady.

08:32.340 --> 08:33.637
Apparently she had
high hopes, too,

08:33.680 --> 08:34.738
but they never panned out.

08:34.780 --> 08:36.941
According to some of
the faculty members I spoke to,

08:36.980 --> 08:38.049
she was pretty difficult.

08:38.080 --> 08:40.014
Just last month,
she was denied tenure.

08:40.050 --> 08:41.574
How'd she take it?

08:41.620 --> 08:42.644
Notgood.

08:42.690 --> 08:44.646
It all blew up at
a faculty meeting a week ago.

08:44.690 --> 08:46.317
She accused Lustig
of rigging the vote.

08:46.350 --> 08:48.079
Did she?
She did.

08:48.120 --> 08:50.224
And according to folks at that
meeting, she really went off.

08:50.260 --> 08:51.249
They had to call

08:51.290 --> 08:52.848
campus security.

08:56.230 --> 08:57.299
CARRIE:
Alwyn?

08:57.330 --> 08:58.661
Alwyn Pierce?

09:00.840 --> 09:02.762
Carrie Wells.
Yeah, we met years ago,

09:02.810 --> 09:04.630
in Gene's first HSAM study.

09:04.670 --> 09:06.308
Yes, I know. I remember.

09:06.340 --> 09:07.671
Lieutenant Al Burns.

09:07.710 --> 09:09.769
Of course.

09:09.810 --> 09:11.107
You're here because of Gene.

09:11.150 --> 09:13.118
You guys worked together
for a long time.

09:13.150 --> 09:14.572
This must be hard for you.

09:14.620 --> 09:15.973
It is.

09:16.020 --> 09:17.089
AL:
Though we understand

09:17.120 --> 09:18.644
you two had
your differences lately.

09:18.690 --> 09:21.818
Perhaps, but
professional squabbles

09:21.860 --> 09:24.078
seem irrelevant
at times like these.

09:24.130 --> 09:25.927
CARRIE:
As opposed to a week ago,

09:25.960 --> 09:26.995
when professional squabbles

09:27.030 --> 09:29.248
led to you being escorted
from a faculty meeting

09:29.300 --> 09:30.961
by four security guards.

09:31.000 --> 09:34.037
I worked with Gene
for ten years.

09:34.070 --> 09:36.095
And I felt I earned his support.

09:36.140 --> 09:38.005
Instead, he blackballed me.

09:38.040 --> 09:40.634
So draw your own conclusions
about our "differences."

09:40.680 --> 09:42.033
Why would he blackball you?

09:42.080 --> 09:43.377
I have no idea.

09:43.410 --> 09:45.674
If he were alive,
you could ask him yourself.

09:45.710 --> 09:47.974
You know, we don't
need to ask him.

09:48.020 --> 09:50.284
According to a transcript
from the tenure committee,

09:50.320 --> 09:52.140
Gene thought
your work displayed--

09:52.190 --> 09:54.818
and I don't think
I'm getting this wrong--

09:54.860 --> 09:56.213
"a shoddy methodology

09:56.260 --> 09:57.750
bordering on fraudulent."

09:57.790 --> 09:59.382
Now, that... that had to hurt.

09:59.430 --> 10:01.796
That was a joke.

10:01.830 --> 10:03.695
Especially since his work

10:03.730 --> 10:04.697
was sloppy and mediocre.

10:04.730 --> 10:06.368
I was a part of Gene's work.

10:06.400 --> 10:08.994
There was nothing mediocre
or sloppy about it.

10:09.040 --> 10:12.032
Where you were between the hours
of 6:00 and 7:00 this morning?

10:12.070 --> 10:13.230
Wait a minute.

10:13.280 --> 10:14.838
I got denied tenure,

10:14.880 --> 10:16.006
and I blame Eugene Lustig,

10:16.040 --> 10:17.678
but I sure as hell
didn't kill him.

10:17.710 --> 10:20.019
_ You sure as hell _
didn't answer my question.

10:20.050 --> 10:23.281
I was asleep,
in my bed, by myself.

10:23.320 --> 10:25.049
You need proof, talk to my cat.

10:25.090 --> 10:27.718
Now, if you'll excuse me,
I have a class to teach.

10:29.760 --> 10:31.785
ELIOT:
She make any physical threats?

10:31.830 --> 10:33.320
"I'll ruin your life.

10:33.360 --> 10:34.759
"You'll regret
what you've done.

10:34.800 --> 10:35.892
You'll be sorry."
That sort of thing.

10:35.930 --> 10:38.160
Sounds like my daily staff
meeting at the mayor's office.

10:38.200 --> 10:39.690
Anything else?

10:39.740 --> 10:41.059
Well, we're trying to find
something more concrete,

10:41.100 --> 10:43.432
see if we can work up a warrant
to search her place.

10:43.470 --> 10:45.199
Please, Burns,
with all deliberate speed?

10:45.240 --> 10:47.800
Algonquian University
pumps $9 billion

10:47.840 --> 10:49.330
into this city's
economy every year.

10:49.380 --> 10:51.871
I know, I thought it was
a typo, too. It's not.

10:51.910 --> 10:53.946
Having this on the front page
of The Times

10:53.980 --> 10:56.175
irritates the mayor,
who then irritates me.

10:56.220 --> 10:57.380
That's a lot
of irritation.

10:57.420 --> 10:58.739
You need more on this woman,

10:58.790 --> 11:00.052
and you're not gonna
find it here.

11:00.090 --> 11:02.115
Would it help to know
that she's a thief?

11:02.160 --> 11:02.922
Check this out.

11:02.960 --> 11:05.827
I followed up
with campus security.

11:05.860 --> 11:07.794
Got them to give me
all the Neuro Lab

11:07.830 --> 11:08.922
surveillance footage
since that faculty meeting

11:08.960 --> 11:09.858
where Alvwn went off.

11:09.900 --> 11:12.425
2:30 a.m., one day
after the tenure meeting.

11:12.470 --> 11:13.391
Alwyn enters the lab,

11:13.440 --> 11:15.829
and she heads for a cabinet
by Lustig's desk.

11:15.870 --> 11:17.337
She opens the cabinet.

11:20.740 --> 11:22.742
Right there. That box.

11:22.780 --> 11:24.702
Security say she was authorized
to be there?

11:24.750 --> 11:26.149
Definitely not.

11:26.180 --> 11:28.478
That's trespassing.

11:28.520 --> 11:29.782
Forget the search warrant.

11:29.820 --> 11:31.788
Go pick her up.
Right.

11:37.330 --> 11:41.221
Alwyn Pierce, I repeat,
this is the NYPD.

11:48.370 --> 11:50.065
MURRAY:
Alwyn Pierce?

11:50.110 --> 11:51.839
Alwyn?

12:01.920 --> 12:04.013
Well, we can rule out
your garden-variety robbery.

12:04.050 --> 12:05.881
Money, credit cards,
all here.

12:05.920 --> 12:07.888
No sign of forced entry,
no struggle.

12:07.920 --> 12:09.217
She let them in.

12:09.260 --> 12:11.125
Yeah, that's how
I read it, too.

12:11.160 --> 12:14.527
Her phone shows one
45-second call at 6:30.

12:14.560 --> 12:17.495
Traces back to a pay phone
at a gas station in Brooklyn.

12:17.530 --> 12:20.033
We'll check
for surveillance cams.

12:34.580 --> 12:36.116
Al?

12:39.960 --> 12:42.212
That's the box Alvwn took
from Lustig's office.

12:42.260 --> 12:44.854
CARRIE: These are tapes
from Gene's HSAM study--

12:44.890 --> 12:46.790
from my HSAM study.

12:49.560 --> 12:51.096
December 3rd was a Friday.

12:51.130 --> 12:52.461
I got off early, so I went

12:52.500 --> 12:55.492
to a 4:30 show
of Unbreakable.

12:55.540 --> 12:57.428
With a friend?
Alone.

12:57.470 --> 12:59.062
It was at the
Syracuse Odeon.

12:59.110 --> 13:00.077
Wow, it was cheap.

13:00.110 --> 13:01.270
It was four bucks.

13:01.310 --> 13:02.572
Any trailers?

13:02.610 --> 13:04.805
Previews. We call them
trailers in New York.

13:04.850 --> 13:06.340
CARRIE: No, I know,
I know what they are.

13:06.380 --> 13:07.517
You all right?

13:07.550 --> 13:09.279
Yeah.
It's just weird, you know?

13:09.320 --> 13:11.083
One thing to
remember something,

13:11.120 --> 13:15.557
it's another thing to
actually see yourself.

13:15.590 --> 13:18.479
That girl doesn't exist anymore.

13:18.530 --> 13:20.327
Those were tough years,

13:20.360 --> 13:21.850
after Syracuse.

13:21.900 --> 13:24.289
Wish I'd been
there to help.

13:24.330 --> 13:26.389
I had to learn to help myself.

13:28.170 --> 13:30.365
Okay, enough of this.

13:30.410 --> 13:33.004
What does it matter if I had
