38:18.760 --> 38:20.079
A few hours, a whole day?

38:20.130 --> 38:21.324
How long?

38:31.000 --> 38:33.662
The first time...

38:33.710 --> 38:36.804
it was a cat.

38:36.840 --> 38:38.774
It was a stupid
neighborhood cat,

38:38.810 --> 38:40.949
and he kept howling and howling.

38:40.980 --> 38:43.949
And when I put my fingers
around its neck,

38:43.980 --> 38:47.416
and I squeezed...

38:47.450 --> 38:50.613
it was like I was here...

38:50.660 --> 38:53.982
for the first time.

38:54.030 --> 38:55.895
Just here, now.

38:55.930 --> 38:59.491
Not five minutes ago,
not 20 minutes ago,

38:59.530 --> 39:01.430
not 20 years ago,

39:01.470 --> 39:04.405
when my father did those things,

39:04.440 --> 39:07.864
and when those boys
did those things,

39:07.910 --> 39:10.037
because I was different.

39:10.080 --> 39:12.503
Because I was the one
who was always telling them

39:12.550 --> 39:15.678
that they were wrong,
because they were always wrong.

39:15.720 --> 39:17.369
They never remembered

39:17.420 --> 39:20.048
anything.

39:20.090 --> 39:23.389
And Valerie...

39:27.430 --> 39:29.819
The last thing I remember

39:29.860 --> 39:33.523
was the light
fading from her eyes

39:33.570 --> 39:37.131
like a torch down a well.

39:37.170 --> 39:40.560
And then it was a miracle.

39:40.610 --> 39:45.445
It was a whole, long,
blissful day of peace.

39:48.080 --> 39:50.071
At least I think it was.

39:52.720 --> 39:54.711
I don't remember.

39:58.590 --> 40:00.581
"Peace"?

40:04.600 --> 40:06.067
I want you

40:06.100 --> 40:09.797
to look at
these women.

40:09.840 --> 40:12.502
I want you to study
their faces.

40:15.680 --> 40:19.571
I want you... to remember them.

40:22.180 --> 40:26.446
Because from now on,
forgetting is not an option.

40:45.240 --> 40:46.730
Nice work.

40:46.770 --> 40:47.930
That was amazing.

41:09.030 --> 41:10.895
There you are.

41:10.930 --> 41:14.195
Carrie Wells, on behalf of
the Memory Studies Group,

41:14.230 --> 41:16.266
it gives me
great pleasure

41:16.300 --> 41:20.009
to present you with
this check for $100 US.

41:20.040 --> 41:22.076
Wow, Gene, $100.

41:23.080 --> 41:26.902
Along with an infinite
amount of gratitude

41:26.950 --> 41:29.612
on behalf of... me.

41:29.650 --> 41:31.686
You know, you can
grow that money,

41:31.720 --> 41:33.244
or you can just
piddle it away.

41:33.290 --> 41:35.155
Maybe I'll do both.

41:35.190 --> 41:36.214
Yeah?

41:36.260 --> 41:37.784
Let me guess.
Texas hold 'em?

41:37.820 --> 41:39.629
Blackjack, actually.

41:39.660 --> 41:40.922
Scientifically sanctioned.

41:40.960 --> 41:42.621
"A little benign forgetting."

41:42.660 --> 41:44.628
Hmm.

41:44.670 --> 41:46.069
What are you
gonna do now?

41:49.640 --> 41:51.608
Keep moving, I guess.

41:51.640 --> 41:55.974
Just a word of advice
from a new old friend?

41:57.840 --> 41:59.649
The past has
lessons for us,

41:59.680 --> 42:01.307
but the present
is where we live.

42:01.350 --> 42:04.786
And nothing brings us into
the present like a goal.

42:04.820 --> 42:07.243
A task that uses

42:07.290 --> 42:09.656
all your powers,
including...

42:12.160 --> 42:13.127
Hmm.

42:13.160 --> 42:14.991
You said you were a cop.

42:17.800 --> 42:19.165
It was too hard.

42:19.200 --> 42:21.191
Okay.

42:23.240 --> 42:26.038
But, Carrie, if anybody
ever needed a mission,

42:26.070 --> 42:27.606
it's you.

42:27.640 --> 42:30.529
When you find one,
let me know.

42:35.650 --> 42:38.619
Gene?

42:38.650 --> 42:40.789
Thank you.

42:57.140 --> 42:58.630
I'm taking off.

42:59.670 --> 43:01.979
Think I'll stick around.

